|movie = ''[[Deadpool & Wolverine]]'' <br> ''[[Avengers: Doomsday]]'' <small>(unreleased)</small><ref>[https://view.email.hollywoodreporter.com/?qs=920806d4f4cbcabf7cd7a2b3562c81022656e755f456b10504e1b64194ca883b33902d70338d3f39a0ef0e586fbbdf3550a137e0d01fcbeb0ed5c1c68417d15038575f6ce226af66 The Hollywood Reporter - Heat Vision]</ref>
|game = ''[[What If...? – An Immersive Story]]''
|actor = [[Ryan Reynolds (actor)|Ryan Reynolds]]<br>[[Nick Pauley]]
|status = Alive}}
{{Quote|I care. I know I turn everything into a joke, but I... I care, and I want to use that feeling for something important. I wanna matter.|Wade Wilson to [[Happy Hogan]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
'''Wade Winston Wilson''' is a [[mutant]] with a powerful healing factor and incredible combat prowess, which led him to work as a notorious mercenary, vigilante, and ally of the [[X-Men/Earth-10005|X-Men]] under the name '''Deadpool'''. He eventually left behind his vigilante lifestyle to find a stable and fulfilling job as a civilian after his attempts to join the [[Avengers]] proved fruitless, until he was taken from his native reality and offered a place in the [[Sacred Timeline]] by [[Mr. Paradox]], a rogue [[Time Variance Authority]] agent. However, after learning that Paradox plotted to annihilate his [[Earth-10005|home timeline]], Deadpool was sent to the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]] alongside a [[Wolverine|Variant]] of his [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]], with whom he formed a very uneasy alliance to escape. The two new friends were able to thwart Paradox's plans and kill [[Cassandra Nova]] before she could erase all timelines, and thus, Wilson invited Logan into his world and continued working for the TVA.

Later on, Deadpool found himself on [[Svartalfheim]] with [[Thor]], where he was injured and his suit was damaged, leaving Thor crying over Deadpool's damaged body.

==Biography==
{{MD|Wade Wilson (Earth-10005 Revised)||1}}
===Early Life===
====Becoming Deadpool====
[[File:When Wade Met Vanessa.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson meets [[Vanessa Carlysle]] at a bar]]
{{Quote|You had a girlfriend?"<br>"Yeah, [[Vanessa Carlysle|Vanessa]], we met when she was a dancer.|[[Wolverine]] and Deadpool|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wade Winston Wilson was born in [[Canada]] and served in the {{WPS|Canadian Special Operations Forces Command}}, but eventually used his superior skills for killing to become a mercenary. Wilson then met [[Vanessa Carlysle]], and the two engaged in intense sexual activity and begun a relationship. Both deeply in love with each other, Wilson proposed to Carlysle, telling her that her crazy matched his crazy.
[[File:Deadpool origins.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson painfully unlocks his mutation]]
But, shorty after, Wilson was diagnosed with an extreme form of cancer throughout his body. Despite having the support of Carlysle, Wilson chose to abandon her to seek experimental treatment from [[Ajax]]. Wilson was put through excruciating torture that caused his [[Mutants|mutation]] to manifest, granting him a regenerative healing factor but disfiguring his entire body in the process. Wilson managed to break out of his captivity, burned down the facility, and fought Ajax, but lost.
[[File:Deadpool reunites with Vanessa.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is reunited with [[Vanessa Carlysle]]]]
Too ashamed to return to Carlysle, Wilson met and moved in with [[Blind Al]], as well as befriending a cab driver named [[Dopinder]]. Carlysle was kidnapped by Ajax, so Wilson, who now donned a [[Deadpool Suit|black and red suit]] and went by the superhero name "Deadpool" to rescue Carlysle. Wilson was aided by [[X-Men/Earth-10005|X-Men]] members [[Colossus]] and [[Negasonic Teenage Warhead]], and was reunited with Carlysle, and the two rekindled their romantic relationship.{{Ref|DW}}

====Life as Deadpool====
[[File:Wade loses Vanessa.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson crying over [[Vanessa Carlysle]]'s body]]
{{Quote|I was... mainly I was team leader... founder, really, of {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}}.|Wade Wilson to [[Happy Hogan]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Eventually, [[Vanessa Carlysle]] was killed sometime later during an attack on Wilson by [[Sergei Valishnikov]]. In an attempt to move on, Wilson joined the [[X-Men/Earth-10005|X-Men]] as a trainee, but it did not work out. 
[[File:Deadpool X-Force.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool leading {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}} on a mission]]
Instead, Wilson decided to form the {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}}, which included [[Shatterstar]] and [[Peter Wisdom]]. However, on their first mission, in which they dealt with {{WPS|Cable (character)#Film|Cable}}, almost all the members of the X-Force were killed when parachuting. Wilson ended up allying with Cable and was able to acquire his [[time travel]] [[Cable's Time-Travel Device|device]]. Wilson used the device to go back in time and save Carlysle from dying.
[[File:Deadpool kills Weapon XI.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool kills another version of [[Weapon XI|himself]]]]
Immediately after, Wilson decided to fix some other things, so he used the Time-Travel Device again to save Wisdom and Shatterstar. In addition to this, Wilson also killed a [[Weapon XI|different version]] of him that was about to face off with [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]]. Wilson then made another stop to a different universe and killed [[Ryan Reynolds]] as he read the script to ''{{WPS|Green Lantern (film)|Green Lantern}}'' before returning to his [[Earth-10005|original universe]].{{Ref|DW}}

====Applying to the Avengers====
[[File:Wade Wilson meets Happy Hogan.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson is interviewed about the [[Avengers]]]]
{{Quote|I need to be an [[Avengers|Avenger]]. Sir, my [[Vanessa Carlysle|girl]]'s kinda had it with my shtick, and if I don't, you know, turn things around and do something with my gifts I don't think it's gonna really work out for me, and I wouldn't blame her.|Wade Wilson to [[Happy Hogan]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
On [[2018|March 14, 2018]], Wilson used [[Cable's Time-Travel Device]] again and traveled to [[Sacred Timeline|Earth-616]] in hopes of becoming an [[Avengers|Avenger]]. He met with [[Happy Hogan]], who he opened up to about his desire to matter, which he wanted to prove to [[Vanessa Carlysle]]. However, Wilson stopped, wondering whether [[Tony Stark]] would be appearing, but Hogan explained that he no longer did meetings, although Wilson initially thought he meant cameos.
[[File:Wade and Happy.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson's is turned down by [[Happy Hogan]]]]
Hogan continued with the interview, and Wilson revealed his time with {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}}, but it only made things worse. Sensing this, Wilson desperately told Hogan that he wanted to be an Avenger because he needed it. Hogan explained to Wilson the importance of being an Avenger, which he included himself a part of, making Wilson question it, asking if his superpower was parallel parking. Hogan told Wilson that the Avengers don't need it, others needed them. Wilson was left disappointed when the interview ended, but listened to Hogan as he advised him to find the place he fits with. Wilson then left the [[Sacred Timeline]] and returned to [[Earth-10005|his universe]] dejected and depressed.{{Ref|DW}}

====Retired Mercenary====
[[File:Wade and Vanessa break up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson is asked to show that he cares]]
{{Quote|I'm done. And I'm fine with being done.|Wade Wilson to [[Peter Wisdom]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wilson destroyed [[Cable's Time-Travel Device]] shortly after returning to [[Earth-10005|his timeline]], where his depression over being denied into the [[Avengers]] grew over time.
[[File:Wade break up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson and [[Vanessa Carlysle]] break up]]
This took a further strain on Wilson's relationship with [[Vanessa Carlysle]], who told him that he needed to show her that he cared about something bigger than himself. Carlysle tried to support Wilson by asking him to let her in, but he instead pushed her away, demanding that she say that she did not want to be with him anymore. The two broke up, and Wilson moved back in with [[Blind Al]], in addition to retiring from his mercenary life. Instead, Wilson got a job at [[Drive Max]], working alongside his best friend and former {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}} teammate, [[Peter Wisdom]].
[[File:It's A Hair System.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson working as a salesman for [[Drive Max]]]]
In [[2020s/Earth-10005#2024|2024]], Wilson tried to sell a {{WPS|Kia Carnival}} to the Chipman family, but because of his constant vulgarity, he failed. At the end of their shift, Wisdom tried to comfort Wilson, telling him that he could always return to being a superhero, revealing that he kept his [[Deadpool Suit|suit]] in his locker. Wilson stated that he was done with that life, although he was not fond over his new one. As they headed home, Wisdom further suggested Wilson go back to doing missions, although Wilson was distracted by construction workers taking photos of him.{{Ref|DW}}

====Celebrating His Birthday====
[[File:Surprise Wade.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson arrives at his surprise birthday party]]
{{Quote|I'm happy. You know, that's because of each and every one of you. I guess what I'm trying to say is how proud I am, how grateful I am, to be standing in a room with every single person I love... I'm the luckiest man alive.|Wade Wilson|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wilson entered his [[Wade Wilson's Apartment|apartment]], where he was surprised by all of his friends waiting for him inside to celebrate his birthday. After a group picture was taken with all of Wilson's friends, the party got started and Wilson mingled with the guests.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (133).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson and [[Blind Al]] talk about doing cocaine]]
Wilson caught up with [[Dopinder]] and [[Shatterstar]], and spoke to [[Blind Al]] about being able to pay the rent, which he was unable to do. Blind Al asked if Wilson wanted to do cocaine, but he told her that it was the one thing [[Kevin Feige]] prohibited them from doing within the [[Deadpool & Wolverine|movie]]. He moved on to [[Colossus]], who revealed he had been watching ''{{WPS|The Great British Bake Off}}'', which Wilson claimed prevented him from suicide.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (8).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson catches up with [[Vanessa Carlysle]]]]
Wilson then gave his opinions on various controversial topics to [[Buck]], but as soon as he went to respond, Wilson stopped Buck, informing him he had no speaking lines. [[Negasonic Teenage Warhead]] commented on Wilson's toupée, but he tried to convince her it was a hair system from the [[France|French]], which [[Yukio]] complimented. Lastly, Wilson spoke with [[Vanessa Carlysle]], who revealed that she was dating [[Dermot|someone]], joking that he had not got her shot yet. The two of them laughed, although Wilson was saddened by Carlysle moving on.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (5).png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson tells his friends he loves them all]]
Everybody then sang "Happy Birthday" to Wilson as they brought out the cake. Wilson gave a speech, reflecting on the difficulty of the past few years and how things had changed for him, but he claimed that he was happy. Wilson credited his happiness to each of his friends, seeing them as the only people that he loved. Wilson finished his speech, stating that he was the luckiest man alive before blowing out the candles.{{Ref|DW}}

===[[Preservation of Earth-10005|Saving His World]]===
====An Offer====
[[File:Time Variance Authority Office (Deadpool & Wolverine).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson in the [[Time Variance Authority Office]]]]
{{Quote|The [[Sacred Timeline]]... I assume I am going to... [[Marvel Cinematic Universe|Marvel]] at how... cinematic it feels? Gratuitous cameos... Indiscriminate use of [[Glossary#V|Variants]], the whole package?|Wade Wilson to [[Mr. Paradox]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Answering a knock at the door, Wilson discovered a squad of [[TVA]] [[Minutemen]] that he assumed were dancers ordered by [[Dopinder]]. As Wilson rattled off several sexual requests to them, a [[Timedoor]] opened behind him and Wilson was forcefully dragged through. Wilson found himself in the [[Time Variance Authority Office|TVA Office]] sitting before [[Mr. Paradox]], who explained the organization to him, which Wilson felt was a lot of exposition for a [[Deadpool & Wolverine|threequel]]. Wilson asked if his abduction was due to him using [[Cable's Time-Travel Device]], but Paradox claimed it was not.
[[File:Paradox & Wade at the TVA.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson is offered the chance to join the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe|MCU]]]]
Paradox asked Wilson to follow him, explaining that he had been chosen for a higher purpose that would prevent a terrible future for the [[Sacred Timeline]], alluding to a potential collaboration with the [[Avengers]]. Wilson caught on to what Paradox was referring to, and subtly responded about the prospect of joining the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]]. Paradox confirmed Wilson's suspicion by showing him footage of [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] and telling him he could also matter. Wilson also spotted a monitor that showed him in [[Thor]]'s arms, making him curious. Wilson excitedly dubbed himself "{{WPS|Marvel Entertainment|Marvel}} {{WPS|Jesus}}" before insulting {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}} and agreed to Paradox's offer.
[[File:Deadpool (TVA).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is provided a [[Deadpool Suit|suit]] from the [[TVA]]]]
Wilson requested a new [[Deadpool Suit|suit]] be made for him, so he met with the TVA's tailor, who adorned Wilson with an improved costume, repeatedly groping him in the process. Wilson was also provided with new weapons, including [[adamantium]] [[Deadpool's Katanas|katanas]]. Deadpool returned to Paradox, expressing his satisfaction with the upgrade, and remarking on [[Ralph (TVA)|Ralph]] being attracted to him. Deadpool asked about bringing his friends over to the [[Sacred Timeline]], but Paradox revealed that he could not returned to his [[Earth-10005|universe]]. Paradox explained that his timeline was decaying due to the [[Glossary#A|Anchor Being]] dying, which Deadpool assumed it was meaning himself, but Paradox laughed at the idea.
[[File:Deadpool at the TVA.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool learns that his [[Earth-10005|universe]] is dying]]
Paradox informed Deadpool that [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]] was the Anchor Being and that his death was the cause of the timeline decaying. Deadpool asked how long his timeline had left, which Paradox responded that it would take a couple thousand years, but he intended to accelerate the process with the [[Time Ripper]]. Deadpool was conflicted upon hearing this, so Paradox gave him the ultimatum once more, only for Deadpool to break Paradox's nose and steal his [[TemPad]] so he could find Wolverine. Deadpool opened a Time Door and escaped.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Battle at Logan's Grave]]====
[[File:Deadpool digs up Logan's grave.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool stands inside [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]]'s grave]]
{{Quote|To be clear, I'm not proud of any of this. The wanton violence, the whiff of necrophilia. It isn't who I am. It isn't who I wanna be.|Deadpool|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool returned to his [[Earth-10005|universe]] in the [[2030s/Earth-10005|2030s]], where he approached [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]]'s grave and begun digging it up. In his narration, Deadpool noted that he was not worried about ruining the legacy of ''{{WPS|Logan (film)|Logan}}'', believing that Wolverine was not actually dead due to his regenerative healing factor. However, Deadpool discovered that Wolverine was truly dead, which enraged him.
[[File:Deadpool with Wolverine's skeleton.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool chats with [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]]'s skeleton]]
Deadpool removed the skeleton from the grave, sat next to it and began talking to it. Deadpool confessed that he had always wanted to team up with Wolverine, thinking it would be a lot of fun but also make [[Ryan Reynolds (actor)|th]][[Hugh Jackman|em]] a lot of money. The [[Minutemen]] found Deadpool and told him to surrender. Deadpool hid with the skeleton and told the Minutemen that he would not surrender, but he did promise not to use any of his weapons, telling the audience that the Human body had two-hundred six bones.
[[File:Deadpool.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool fights against the [[TVA]] [[Minutemen]]]]
Holding Wolverine's skeleton, Deadpool stood before the Minutemen and used the bones to violently kill them. In between the fight, Deadpool would break the fourth wall and dance to "{{WPS|Bye Bye Bye}}" by [[*NSYNC]]. After using all of Wolverine's bones, Deadpool attached his retractable bone claws to his suit. Deadpool had some difficulty using the claws, including stabbing his own arm, as well as getting the claws stuck in two Minutemen. Once only the leader was left, Deadpool bounced his [[Deadpool's Katanas|katana]] into his face after he insulted [[Canada]]. Deadpool then used the [[TemPad]] to leave and find another [[Hub:Logan|Wolverine]].{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Search for Wolverine|Finding a Wolverine]]====
[[File:Deadpool meets Wolverine.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool meets a comic accurate [[Wolverine/Short Wolverine|Logan]]]]
{{Quote|Why would I go with you?"<br>"Because, unfortunately, I need you. And even more unfortunately, my [[Earth-10005|entire world]] needs you.|[[Wolverine]] and Deadpool|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool commenced his search across the [[Multiverse]], where he first found a [[Wolverine/Short Wolverine|Wolverine]] whose height was comic-accurate in [[Short Wolverine Universe|his universe]]. Deadpool found his height adorable and left through a [[Timedoor]]. The [[Amputee Wolverine Universe|next universe]] Deadpool arrived in was more apocalyptic, and he came across [[Weapon X]], who immediately started beating him up, so he left.
[[File:Wolverine meets Deadpool.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool searching for another [[Hub:Logan|Wolverine]]]]
The following Variant Deadpool encountered was [[Patch]], who also responded with aggression by stabbing him in the head. Other Variants Deadpool encountered included an [[Wolverine/Old Man Logan|older version of Logan]] who shot him, a [[Wolverine/Crucified Wolverine|Wolverine]] that had been crucified on top of a sea of skulls, and a [[Wolverine/Hulk Fighter Wolverine|Wolverine]] donning the classic {{WPS|John Byrne (comics)|John Byrne}} [[Wolverine Suit|brown-and-tan suit]], but was attacked by an alternate [[Hulk/Hulk Fighter Wolverine|Hulk]]. Deadpool was excited when meeting the next Wolverine, played by [[Henry Cavill]], thus dubbed the "[[Cavillrine]]," who also attacked Deadpool, despite Deadpool saying they would treat him better than {{WPS|DC Entertainment|DC}} did.
[[File:Deadpool and Logan.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool tells [[Wolverine]] to come with him]]
Falling through the Timedoor into a bar, Deadpool spotted another [[Wolverine]] and approached him. Deadpool told Wolverine to come with him to help save his [[Earth-10005|world]], only to be met with refusal. Running out of time and not being immediately attacked, Deadpool decided to drag Wolverine from his stool. Wolverine resisted being taken, so Deadpool pulled his gun on him, only for Wolverine to finish off an entire bottle, causing him to pass out. Being short on other options, Deadpool decided to take this Wolverine back with him. But before picking him up, Deadpool noticed that Wolverine was wearing his [[Wolverine Suit|iconic suit]] underneath his clothes.
[[File:Deadpool and Wolverine at the TVA.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool threatens to expose [[Mr. Paradox]]]]
Deadpool returned to the [[Time Variance Authority Office]] with the drunk Wolverine in his suit, telling [[Mr. Paradox]] that he had found a replacement Anchor Being. However, Paradox informed Deadpool that it did not work that way, but also that he had found the worst Wolverine in the Multiverse. Desperate, Deadpool asked what could be done, but Paradox stated that he already gave Deadpool the chance to join the [[Sacred Timeline]], and nothing else could be done to save his world. When Wolverine got up, Deadpool welcomed him into the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe|MCU]], saying it was currently at a low point. Deadpool then realized that Paradox was working rogue of the [[TVA]], so Paradox pruned him before he could expose their actions.{{Ref|DW}}

====Sent to the Void====
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (120).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is pruned and sent to the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]]]
{{Quote|Those pricks in the [[TVA]], you heard them. They have the power to end my [[Earth-10005|universe]], but they also have the power to change [[Mutant Genocide Universe|yours]]. We get back there and we can fix your world together. I promise.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool was sent to the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], where he was attacked by [[Wolverine]] who asked where they both were, but Deadpool did not know, claiming it looked similar to the {{WPS|Mad Max|''Mad Max'' franchise}}, though it would be IP infringement if that were the case.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (36).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool demands [[Wolverine]] to help him]]
Deadpool urged that they needed to get back to [[Mr. Paradox]] before his [[Earth-10005|world]] was destroyed but Wolverine did not care. Deadpool brought up Wolverine letting down his own world, causing Wolverine to once again attack Deadpool by stabbing him in the back. Deadpool maneuvered himself and slammed Wolverine to the ground, allowing him to unload his clips into Wolverine's sides. Deadpool asked if Wolverine was going to be calm, but Wolverine answered by throwing Deadpool into the {{WPS|20th Century Studios|20th Century Fox}} logo.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (87).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool fighting with [[Wolverine]] in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]]]
The two stood at opposite ends of each other about to fight, but Deadpool claimed he did not want to, although Wolverine did not care. Knowing that it was what the audience wanted to see, Deadpool prepared to face off with Wolverine, despite knowing how much it would hurt. Swiftly reloading his guns, Deadpool fired upon a fast approaching Wolverine, until they were sliced by his claws. Deadpool equipped his [[Deadpool's Katanas|katanas]] and the two stabbed each other repeatedly, with Deadpool leaving his katanas in Wolverine's body.
[[File:Wolverine, Deadpool, and Johnny Storm.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is excited by "[[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Captain America]]"]]
Deadpool stopped the fight by promising Wolverine that the [[TVA]] could change whatever went wrong in his world. Wolverine yielded and they overheard a voice call out to them saying that they should not fight each other. Deadpool was in awe, believing that he was seeing [[Hub:Steve Rogers|Captain America]], who pointed out [[Cassandra Nova's Henchmen|enemies]] approaching. As the three were surrounded, Deadpool expected to hear the iconic "Avengers Assemble" battle cry, only to be confused when the person turned out to be [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Human Torch]], who was quickly defeated by [[Pyro]].
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Nice (12).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool attempts to give [[Wolverine]] advice]]
They then spotted [[Sabretooth]], who challenged Wolverine to fight, so Deadpool took a timeout to pull his katanas out of Wolverine while giving him advice to defeating his brother. However, Wolverine told Deadpool to shut up, so he stood back and watched eagerly as the two charged at each other. The fight was quickly over as Wolverine took one slash at Sabretooth and decapitated him. Deadpool picked up Sabretooth's head and taunted the rest of the enemies, but he and Wolverine were incapacitated by a giant magnet and knocked out by a leg of a [[Sentinels|Sentinel]].
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine -BestFriendsDay (19).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] agree to team up]]
Deadpool, Wolverine and Human Torch were tied up and placed in a cage together. When they awoke, Human Torch explained where they were, and that everything present is annihilated by [[Alioth]], which Deadpool knew from ''[[Loki (TV series)|Loki]]'' [[Loki (TV series)/Season One|Season One]] [[Journey Into Mystery|Episode Five]]. They also learned of a [[Resistance]] of heroes, so Wolverine determined they could help them escape the Void, so Deadpool happily agreed to the team-up. Human Torch warned them about [[Cassandra Nova]], who he used vulgar language to describe, and told Deadpool he could be quoted.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Escape from Cassandra Nova's Lair|Meeting Cassandra Nova]]====
[[File:Deadpool Wolverine.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool being brought to [[Cassandra Nova]]]]
{{Quote|This may be hard to hear, but there's another [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Mr. Paradox|villain]]. He's gonna destroy my [[Earth-10005|universe]], and I'm gonna stop him."<br>"Oh, honey, you don't really strike me as the world-saving type. Did I hit a nerve?|Deadpool and [[Cassandra Nova]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
The three prisoners arrived at [[Cassandra Nova's Lair]], which was the skeleton of a dead [[Giant-Man/Giant-Man Pruned|Giant-Man]], which Deadpool joked about [[Paul Rudd]] finally aging. Deadpool then thought they were being greeted by [[Professor X/Cassandra Nova Birthed|Professor X]], but instead it was Nova in his [[Charles Xavier's Wheelchair|wheelchair]]. Nova explained her backstory and decided to free Deadpool and [[Wolverine]].
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine in the Void.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool's actions get [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Human Torch]] killed]]
When Nova turned her attention to [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Human Torch]], Deadpool revealed that they were told all about Nova by him. Wolverine and Human Torch tried to get Deadpool to stop talking, but he continued, quoting in exact crude detail what was said about Nova. Human Torch desperately denied everything, but Nova ruthlessly ripped off his skin, instantly killing him. Wolverine blamed Deadpool for his death, but Deadpool just responded that [[Chris Evans|he]] was not his favorite [[Chris Hemsworth|Ch]][[Chris Pratt|ris]], and that his presence was impacting the [[Deadpool & Wolverine|movie]]'s budget.
[[File:Wolverine & Deadpool (Void).jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool asks [[Cassandra Nova]] for her help]]
Nova pointed out [[Alioth]]'s arrival, but Deadpool attempted to explain his predicament, needing to save his [[Earth-10005|world]], which Nova claimed Deadpool was not the world-saving type. This silenced Deadpool, and Nova picked up on it being a sensitive subject for him. Deadpool demanded that Nova helped them. They then listened as Nova talked about how the [[TVA]] sent her to the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], but Deadpool did not care for her trauma bragging. Wolverine went to attack Nova, so she used her powers to bury him underground. Deadpool asked Nova to help him escape the Void, which she revealed that she was capable of doing but refused.
[[File:Deadpool looks at Alioth.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is denied help by [[Cassandra Nova]]]]
Instead, Nova phased her fingers through Deadpool's head, which allowed her to access his mind. Nova searched through Deadpool's memories, and manipulated one with [[Vanessa Carlysle]] to have her say that Deadpool would never matter. Deadpool was able to break out of Nova's hold, and Wolverine returned and they attacked her; however, it did no damage. Nova retreated as Alioth began to swarm the compound, so Deadpool and Wolverine escaped using the rocket on a [[Sentinels|Sentinel]]'s leg.{{Ref|DW}}

====Navigating the Void====
[[File:Whatcha thinkin bout.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] manage to escape]]
{{Quote|If there's a chance [[Resistance|they]] know how to get outta [[Void (End of Time)|here]], we find them and make those [[TVA]] fuckers fix my shit like you fucking promised."<br>"I smell quest.|[[Wolverine]] and Deadpool|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] crash-landed upon a cliff. Wolverine snapped at Deadpool, saying that he would do the talking from now on, which Deadpool felt would be hard for the audience. Wolverine then mapped out their plan to get back to [[Mr. Paradox]] by finding the [[Resistance]] and getting them to help them escape the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]].
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine -BestFriendsDay (6).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool asks [[Wolverine]] about his past]]
The two stopped by [[Joe's Diner]], where Deadpool asked Wolverine about his [[Wolverine Suit|costume]], claiming that [[Deadpool Suit|his]] was red so that no one could see him bleed. Wolverine asked if Deadpool had been checked for ADHD, but Deadpool just joked that he probably got several STDs because of it. Wolverine pointed out the spots of hair from Deadpool's toupée, stating that it was obvious he wore one. Deadpool brought up his [[Earth-10005|universe]]'s [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]] being the ultimate hero, and talked about how he wanted to also matter, but had only been rejected by everyone.
[[File:Wolverine, Dogpool & Wade Wilson.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool encounters [[Dogpool]] in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]]]
As they walked, Wolverine asked what happened to his Variant, so Deadpool revealed that he died while trying to save [[X-23]]. Deadpool passed on advice from [[Blind Al]] to Wolverine, in that he needed to listen to his pain instead of running from it as it can teach people who they are. They then saw a [[Dogs|dog]] in a Deadpool costume run towards them and jump into Deadpool's arms. Deadpool wanted to bring the dog with them, but Wolverine was against it. They were then joined by a handsome Variant of Deadpool named [[Nicepool]], who owned the dog and possessed a pair of gold-plated Desert Eagles that Deadpool wanted.
[[File:D&W meet Nicepool.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool listens to [[Nicepool]] give directions]]
Nicepool introduced them to [[Dogpool]], who Deadpool let lick his mouth. Deadpool was annoyed at how nice and good looking his Variant was, and asked about the Resistance. Nicepool confirmed their existence, but also warned the two about the [[Deadpool Corps]]. Nicepool offered his them his [[Ol' Betsy|ride]] to get to the borderlands, but when Deadpool discovered that it was a {{WPS|Honda Odyssey (North America)|Honda Odyssey}} he was adamantly against driving it. Nicepool asked for Dogpool back, which Deadpool was reluctant to do, wanting to keep her.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Duel in Ol' Betsy|Fight with Wolverine]]====
[[File:Spider-Pool.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] driving together]]
{{Quote|I don't know anything about saving worlds, and why would I even care? Because my entire world is right here in this picture. It's only nine people, and I have no idea how to save it alone.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
As they drove, Deadpool again asked [[Wolverine]] about his [[Wolverine Suit|costume]], wondering why he would wear it, but Wolverine insisted he stop talking about it. Instead, Deadpool mimicked [[Spider-Man]]'s [[Web-Shooters]], much to Wolverine's annoyance.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (60).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool tells [[Wolverine]] about his friends]]
Deadpool questioned what Wolverine would do if the [[TVA]] could fix his [[Mutant Genocide Universe|world]]. Wolverine abruptly stopped the car, realizing that Deadpool had no clue whether the TVA could actually change what happened to his world so he stabbed him in the leg. Deadpool defended his actions by saying he made an educated wish, and that it was all so he could get Wolverine to help save his world. Showing Wolverine a picture of his friends, Deadpool told him that they were his whole world and that he did not know how to save them, but Wolverine did.
[[File:Deadpool Pre-Stab Wolverine.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool furiously fights against [[Wolverine]]]]
Enraged, Wolverine proceeded to viciously insult Deadpool, calling him a joke and agreeing with the [[Avengers]] and [[X-Men/Earth-10005|X-Men]]'s decision not to recruit him. Wolverine added that in his entire existence, he had never met anyone as pitiful as Deadpool and not only reiterated [[Cassandra Nova]]'s point about him never being able to save the world but used it to cruelly mock his failure to keep [[Vanessa Carlysle]] in his love life. Deadpool was silent after Wolverine's harsh words, and gently responded that he was going to fight Wolverine. The two then violently brawled in the car until they both tired out.{{Ref|DW}}

====Meeting the Resistance====
[[File:Deadpool wakes up.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool inside of the [[Hero Hideout]]]]
{{Quote|This is what I'm talking about; big slow-motion fight, sad music, everybody working together, who knows if you live or die, that sort of thing. Who's ready!?|Deadpool to the [[Resistance]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool woke up inside a [[Hero Hideout|hideout]], with neither he or [[Wolverine]] knowing how they got there. Hearing someone approaching, Deadpool rushed to attack them, but was immediately bested and dropped to the floor by [[Elektra/Forgotten Elektra|Elektra]]. Deadpool yielded, and witnessed as [[Blade/Universe Defender Blade|Blade]] and [[Gambit]] joined them, leading Deadpool to realize they were the [[Resistance]].
[[File:Deadpool asks Elektra her name.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool greets the [[Resistance]] members]]
Deadpool greeted each member individually, starting with Elektra, who he mistook for {{WPS|Wonder Woman}}, then Blade, who Deadpool thought was retired and alluded to their {{WPS|Blade: Trinity|past together}}, and then concluding with Gambit, who he mocked for his incomprehensible accent and his {{WPS|Gambit (unproduced film)|film that was never made}}. Deadpool learned that there was a fourth member, and hoped it was [[Magneto/Earth-10005|Magneto]], only to be informed that he was dead, causing Deadpool to curse [[Walt Disney Studios|Disney]] for now deciding to be cheap.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Purpose (29).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool decides to join the [[Resistance]]]]
They were joined by [[X-23]], who Deadpool notified Wolverine of her being [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|his]] daughter that he previously mentioned. Deadpool asked how the Resistance ended up in the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], so they told him that the [[TVA]] showed up, told them their universes were dying, and refused to let them fight for it, but instead pruned them when they resisted. Deadpool inserted himself onto the team to get out of the Void, although Wolverine interjected, warning the Resistance that Deadpool was a liar.
[[File:Deadpool mourns Johnny.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool listening to the [[Resistance]]'s past]]
Deadpool revealed to the Resistance that he and Wolverine had [[Escape from Cassandra Nova's Lair|escaped]] from [[Cassandra Nova]]'s [[Cassandra Nova's Lair|compound]], and that Nova was the only way out of the Void. However, none of them believed Deadpool, stating that each time they had gone up against Nova, they lost members, including [[Daredevil/Forgotten Elektra|Daredevil]], who Deadpool gave his condolences for to Elektra, but she was not too affected by it. Gambit also mentioned [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Human Torch]] going missing, so Deadpool pretended to not know him.
[[File:Deadpool Avenge.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool asking the [[Resistance]] to help him]]
Sensing that the Resistance were in need of motivation, Deadpool tried to convince them that by working together they could force Nova to comply with them. Deadpool told them that they would still be able to avenge their universes, claiming that it was what Human Torch would have wanted. At the mention of Human Torch, Elektra asked how Deadpool knew him, so Wolverine outed Deadpool for getting him killed. Deadpool defended himself, blaming Human Torch for his own demise, and circled back to getting the Resistance to help save his [[Earth-10005|world]].
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (124).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool motivates the [[Resistance]] to fight]]
Elektra had no interest in saving Deadpool's world, but she was intrigued by their chances of defeating Nova, so he suggested they use Magneto's [[Magneto's Helmet|helmet]] to block Nova's psychic powers, only to find out that the helmet had been melted by Nova. Elektra proposed using [[Juggernaut]]'s [[Juggernaut's Helmet|helmet]], which Gambit commented on, but Deadpool could not understand him. The Resistance were inspired by Deadpool to fight back and get their ending, which Deadpool was hyped by, only for Wolverine to bring down the mood by stating that they'd all die.{{Ref|DW}}

====[[Assault on Cassandra Nova's Lair|Escaping the Void]]====
[[File:Resistance Riders.png|{{AltFloat}}|The [[Resistance]] discuss their plan of attack]]
{{Quote|I just need to get [[Earth-10005|home]].|Deadpool to [[Cassandra Nova]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
The next morning, as the [[Resistance]] approached [[Cassandra Nova]]'s [[Cassandra Nova's Lair|compound]], Deadpool tried to translate for [[Gambit]], only to give up and tell the camera to tilt up to [[Blade/Universe Defender Blade|Blade]]. Deadpool asked where Blade's weapon came from, [[Elektra/Forgotten Elektra|Elektra]] answered that it was [[Punisher/AT4 Owner Punisher|Punshier]]'s {{WPS|AT4}}. Deadpool wondered which [[Hub:Frank Castle|Punisher]], due to the several iterations. Blade commented that he was the only Blade, but Deadpool looked to the camera, knowing there would be [[Blade|another]].
[[File:Resistance Assemble.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool standing with the [[Resistance]]]]
Blowing up the entrance, the Resistance drove inside the compound, exited ''[[Ol' Betsy]]'', and stood together while being surrounded by Nova's [[Cassandra Nova's Henchmen|henchmen]]. The two sides charged at each other and commenced fighting. The Resistance pushed forward until Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] were inside. The two confronted Nova, who had been expecting them, and Deadpool asked her to take them [[Earth-10005|home]], but she refused. Nova used her powers to attack Deadpool, slamming him into the ceiling before throwing him across the room.
[[File:Nova with helmet on.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool blocks [[Cassandra Nova]]'s powers]]
The rest of the Resistance managed to steal [[Juggernaut]]'s [[Juggernaut's Helmet|helmet]], and [[X-23]] threw it to Deadpool. While Nova was in Wolverine's mind, Deadpool snuck up on her and put the helmet on her head, neutralizing her psychic abilities. Deadpool then demanded Nova send them home or he would kill her. However, Nova revealed that she could only do that with the helmet removed, and as soon as they would do that, she would instantly kill them. With no other choice, Deadpool and Wolverine then argued over which one of them would kill Nova.
[[File:Deadpool and Wolverine jumping into a portal.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] escaping the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]]]]
At that moment, Nova was shot by [[Pyro]] and would soon die, so Wolverine told Deadpool to remove the helmet. Deadpool was hesitant to do so, but Wolverine told him that he finally felt like an [[X-Men/Mutant Genocide|X-Man]] and that [[Professor X/Mutant Genocide|Professor X]] would not want Nova to die. Wolverine removed the helmet, and Nova decided not to kill them, but instead opened a [[Inter-Dimensional Portal|portal]] with a [[Sling Ring]] to Deadpool's universe. Deadpool and Wolverine jumped through the portal before [[Alioth]] ate them.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Everyone (21).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool jokes on [[Hugh Jackman]]'s return]]
The portal brought them above [[Drive Max]], causing Deadpool and Wolverine to crash in front of [[Peter Wisdom]] and the Chipman family. The children were in awe of seeing the two superheroes, particularly Wolverine, so Deadpool commented that [[Walt Disney Studios|Disney]] were going to make [[Hugh Jackman]] play the role until he was ninety years old. As they left, Deadpool told Wisdom to clock him out forever, confirming his return to being a superhero.{{Ref|DW}}

====Fighting the Deadpool Corps====
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Purpose (19).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool learns [[Cassandra Nova]]'s intent]]
{{Quote|With the whole [[Multiverse]] [[The Multiverse Saga|thing]]. It's not great. It's just been miss after miss after miss. Look, ''{{WPS|The Wizard of Oz}}'' did the Multiverse first and they did it best. The gays knew it, but we didn't listen. Let's just take the L and move on.|Deadpool to the [[Deadpool Corps]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] rushed to the subway entrance outside his [[Wade Wilson's Apartment|apartment]] where they confronted [[Mr. Paradox]]. Deadpool immediately asked why [[Thor]] was crying in his future, but Paradox ignored the question. They witnessed a [[Inter-Dimensional Portal|portal]] open up, and [[Cassandra Nova]] came through. Nova entered Paradox's mind and learned about the [[Time Ripper]], which she intended to use, so she launched Deadpool and Wolverine away, crashing into [[Liefeld's]] and knocking them out.
[[File:Dogpool Loves Deadpool.jpg|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool lovingly embracing [[Dogpool]]]]
When Deadpool and Wolverine got back up, they witnessed [[Dogpool]] come through the portal, much to the joy of Deadpool, who embraced her. However, this bliss was ruined when [[Nicepool]] arrived out of the portal and asked for Dogpool to be returned to him. Deadpool wanted Dogpool to choose who her owner should be, mockingly referring to Nicepool as "{{WPS|Van Wilder|Van Milder}}." Nicepool enjoyed the reference and claimed he also had fourth wall awareness, which he demonstrated by looking into the camera and saying "''{{WPS|The Proposal (2009 film)|The Proposal}}''." Although Deadpool was insulted by how he broke the fourth wall in comparison to himself.
[[File:Deadpool hates the Multiverse.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool addressing the [[Deadpool Corps]]]]
Wolverine told them both to stop talking, revealing that he could smell a lot more Deadpools incoming. They witnessed [[Deadpool Corps]] emerge out of the portal, having been sent by Nova to protect her. Deadpool handed Dogpool to Wolverine and went to speak with the Corps. Deadpool asked if they could just be done, but [[Ladypool]] insisted that they fight. However, Deadpool clarified that he meant being done with the [[Multiverse]] [[The Multiverse Saga|narrative]], claiming it had not been great, and that only the "''{{WPS|The Wizard of Oz}}''" did it right.
[[File:Nicepool Death.PNG|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool deliberately gets [[Nicepool]] killed]]
The Corps told Deadpool that Nova will destroy the Multiverse with the Time Ripper and that they couldn't stop her. The Corps then fired upon the three, so Deadpool used Nicepool as a shield while getting to cover. Wolverine accused Deadpool of getting Nicepool shot on purpose, but Deadpool dismissed it. Nicepool revealed that he did not have a healing factor, so Deadpool dragged him over to a nearby donut stand across the street to save him, only for the Corps to continue shooting Nicepool until he died.
[[File:Wolverine&Deadpool.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] before the fight]]
Wolverine joined Deadpool on the other side of the street, where Deadpool had already stolen the golden pistols from Nicepool's corpse. Deadpool asked Wolverine if he was ready to fight, and the two walked back out. Wolverine put on his mask, which Deadpool was excited to finally see, and the two charged at the army of Deadpools. Deadpool used his new guns but soon ran out of bullets, so he proceeded to use his [[Deadpool's Katanas|katanas]] to stab several Deadpools, as well as using [[Headpool]] as a weapon.
[[File:Deadpool&Wolverine.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] defeat the [[Deadpool Corps|Corps]]]]
Together, Deadpool and Wolverine were able to clear through the entirety of the Corps, violently stabbing and slicing all of them. The fight was ended with the two of them jumping out of a bus window, only for Deadpool to not stick the landing, which disappointed him. They noticed [[Babypool]] laughing at them, which confused Deadpool, only to turn around and see all of the Deadpools getting back up, as they could regenerate, which frustrated Deadpool as they needed to stop Nova.
[[File:Deadpool saved by Peter.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is surprised by [[Peterpool]]'s arrival]]
Before another fight began, they were saved by the arrival of [[Peter Wisdom]], who was wearing his Deadpool's old suit. To Deadpool's surprise, all of the Corps were thrilled to see Wisdom, revealing that every [[Hub:Wade Wilson|Deadpool]] in the Multiverse had their own [[Hub:Peter Wisdom|Wisdom]]. The Corps then cheered and bombarded Wisdom with praise, so Deadpool and Wolverine took the opportunity to sneak away from the Corps and make their way down the subway to deal with Nova.{{Ref|DW}}

====Finally Mattering====
[[File:Threatening Mr Paradox.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool is given the stakes by [[Mr. Paradox]]]]
{{Quote|You were right. One of us would have been killed. But you put a Deadpool and a [[Wolverine]] together, make them hold hands while listening to {{WPS|Madonna}}? Indestructible, motherfucker.|Deadpool to [[Mr. Paradox]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Deadpool and Wolverine found [[Mr. Paradox]], who told them they were too late to stop [[Cassandra Nova]]. Deadpool promised the audience they were nearing the end of the movie, and asked Paradox explain what the stakes were. Paradox revealed that they could stop Nova from destroying all timelines by creating a circuit between the matter and antimatter feeds, but it would annihilate whichever one of them chose to do it.
[[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Final Trailer (3).png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool says his goodbye to [[Wolverine]]]]
As they rushed to the feeds, Wolverine stopped to remind Deadpool that stopping Nova would be fatal. Deadpool decided that he would sacrifice himself, feeling bad for dragging Wolverine into the situation and lying about being able to save his world. Wolverine forgave Deadpool, and showed Deadpool the picture of his friends who he needed to get back to, unlike Wolverine who had no one. Wolverine went to make the sacrifice, so Deadpool told him that he waited a long time for them to team up and that he was the best [[Hub:Logan|Wolverine]].
[[File:Deadpool Noble Sacrifice.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool decides to sacrifice himself]]
But, once Wolverine opened the door, Deadpool hit him in the face with a fire extinguisher and swapped places with him. Wolverine demanded that Deadpool open the door, but he refused, determined to make his "noble sacrifice," once again claiming that he was [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]] {{WPS|Jesus}}. Deadpool told Wolverine to say hi to his friends for him, but Wolverine told Deadpool that he didn't need to do it. However, Deadpool, having learned the lesson from [[Happy Hogan]], stated that he was not doing it because he needed it, but because they did.
[[File:Wolverine and Deadpool hold hands.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] create a circuit]]
Deadpool then pulled out one of the feeds and tried to reach over to the other side to create the circuit, but it was too far away. Wolverine managed to break down the door, grabbed Deadpool's hand and put his claws through the other feed, creating the circuit. Wolverine's top was ripped off him, exposing his abs, which Deadpool nodded in approval to the camera. As the matter and antimatter painfully surged through their bodies, Deadpool and Wolverine looked at each other with acceptance, and were able to short-circuit the [[Time Ripper]], destroying it.
[[File:Deadpool and Wolverine Slow-Mo Walk.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool and [[Wolverine]] manage to survive]]
Deadpool and Wolverine were able to survive the obliteration, due to them sharing the matter and antimatter between them. They returned to Paradox, who thought they had been killed, and Deadpool told him that this Wolverine was the new anchor being for his [[Earth-10005|universe]]. After making Wolverine cover up, Deadpool told Paradox that one of them would have died, but the two of them holding hands while listening to "{{WPS|Like a Prayer}}" made them indestructible.
[[File:Logan and Deadpool.png|{{AltFloat}}|Deadpool learns that his universe is saved]]
[[B-15]] went to have Deadpool pruned, but [[Peter Wisdom]] arrived, informing her that he was from this universe. B-15 revealed to them that their actions saved Deadpool's universe from extinction, and that their work was just getting started, making Deadpool joke again about [[Hugh Jackman]] being Wolverine until he was ninety years old. Deadpool asked B-15 to free the [[Resistance]] members from the [[Void (End of Time)|Void]], which she approved. But when Deadpool asked about fixing Wolverine's past, she informed them that it led to him saving the [[Multiverse]], so it couldn't be changed.{{Ref|DW}}

====Celebrating Victory====
[[File:D&W Shawarma.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson and [[Logan]] relaxing in the aftermath]]
{{Quote|Everyone wants to matter. Turns out that you don't need to be [[Marvel Studios|Marvel]] {{WPS|Jesus}} to do it. You just need to open your eyes and look around. And if you're lucky, you'll find a few friends. Old friends and some new ones, too.|Wade Wilson|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
Wilson and [[Logan]] went to get some shawarma, quipping that the [[Avengers]] discovered it. Wilson was overjoyed to see [[Dogpool]] was still around, and he picked her up. Wilson asked about Logan's plans, and he responded that he probably would not see him again. As Logan walked away, Wilson called out to him and asked him to stay. Logan obliged, and they headed up to Wilson's [[Wade Wilson's Apartment|apartment]], where Wilson introduced [[Blind Al]] to Logan and Dogpool. 
[[File:Wade smiling at Vanessa.png|{{AltFloat}}|Wilson and [[Vanessa Carlysle]] finally rekindle]]
[[B-15]] followed through with her promise and Wilson and Logan were reunited with [[Laura]], who also decided to stay with them. Later on, Wilson had another party at his apartment with all of his friends, now joined by Logan, Laura and Dogpool. As they all sat around laughing, Logan told Wilson to talk to [[Vanessa Carlysle]]. Wilson told Carlysle that he saved the [[Multiverse]] for her, and she responded by holding his hand, rekindling their relationship as they smiled at each other.{{Ref|DW}}

