==Powers and Abilities==
===Powers===
{{Quote|Motherfucker, I wish I could say you'll die alone, but it's one of God's best jokes that you can't die!|[[Logan]] to Deadpool|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''Mutant Physiology''': Wilson was naturally born with dormant mutant genes that were artificially triggered through torturous experimentation. His physiology was drastically altered after he survived the experience, becoming deformed in the process and also awakening several special abilities.
**'''Superhuman Strength''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (79).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool slices through a soldier's armor]] Wilson's strength has been enhanced to superhuman levels, as he effortlessly broke [[Mr. Paradox]]'s nose with a headbutt. He also systematically broke off pieces of his [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Logan]]'s [[Adamantium]] skeleton as improvised weapons against TVA soldiers, and was even able to use the blunt ends of his bones to pierce their armor; in one instance, he impaled one soldier through his helmet and kicked it out the other side of his head. Throughout his fights against [[Wolverine]], Wilson was able to match his rival's equally superhuman physical strength, notably giving him a nosebleed with a single punch and even kicking him several meters through the windshield of [[Nicepool]]'s Honda Odyssey. During [[Cassandra Nova]]'s absorption of the [[Time Ripper]]'s power as part of her plot to destroy all timelines, Wilson easily punched open the [[Time Ripper]]'s matter chamber and pulled out the matter feed, intending to reach the anti-matter chamber and create a circuit, although the anti-matter chamber was too far away.
**'''Superhuman Durability''': [[File:Wolverine lifts Deadpool.png|thumb|250px|Deadpool endures [[Wolverine]]'s claws]] Wilson's durability and endurance have been enhanced to superhuman levels. Coupled with his regenerative factor, the extremely high level of durability meant that Deadpool could engage in fights with enemies for a very long period of time, as shown when he fought Wolverine in point-blank range without rest for a few hours. He repeatedly took stabs to various parts of his body (including his gut and head) but still continued.
**'''Superhuman Speed''': Wilson can run very fast, as he and Wolverine were able to reach [[Cassandra Nova]]'s portal in four seconds before they could be consumed by [[Alioth]].
**'''Superhuman Agility''': Wilson's agility and body coordination are enhanced well-beyond the natural physical limits of a common human being.
**'''Superhuman Stamina''': Wilson can exert himself for longer than any normal human, as he [[Duel in Ol' Betsy|fought]] [[Wolverine]] for the majority of a day in the confined space of [[Nicepool]]'s Honda Odyssey.
**'''Superhuman Reflexes''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (90).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool catching a magazine with his gun]] Wilson has superhumanly acute reflexes as a result of his artificial mutation. Hence, he can react quickly in a combat scenario, enough to keep pace with multiple [[Time Variance Authority|TVA]] soldiers, slice bullets mid air with his katanas (albeit with minimal success) and contend with [[Wolverine]]. In one instance, he caught two spare magazines with his pistols. He was able to catch an axe thrown at him while walking through a [[Timedoor]].
**'''Regenerative Healing Factor''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (99).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool heals his arm]] As a result of his artificial mutation, Wilson's body was enhanced and he developed extremely accelerated healing and regenerative powers. He can heal from any injury (both internal and external), such as bullet wounds, slashes, and other forms of cuts in seconds. For example, he could almost immediately realign his arm, which was forcefully broken by Wolverine. He even took stabs to his head, but was able to survive. He managed to regrow lost organs and bodily parts, but those take more time to recover when compared to injuries that do not involve the loss of body parts.
***'''Pain Suppression''': Due to his healing factor, his body can suppress the immense amount of pain caused during fights, which usually end with him seriously injured.
***'''Nigh-Immortality''': Due to his regenerative capabilities, Wilson is immune to physical aging. He is also virtually impossible to kill and cannot be infected by any kind of disease, as well as a weapon capable of destroying a universe, along with [[Wolverine]]. Wolverine even remarked in frustration at how Wilson cannot die.
{{Quote|I smell what you're stepping in. The power in the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe|Marvel universe]] is about to change forever.|Deadpool to [[Mr. Paradox]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''4th Wall Awareness''': [[File:I'm Going To Disneyland.png|thumb|250px|Deadpool interacting with the microphone]] Deadpool possesses an awareness that he is a fictional character existing within a film franchise. This ability penetrates deeper into the real world than [[She-Hulk]], who is only able to access a lesser version of reality that mirrors the real world. Before he was given the offer to join the Sacred Timeline, Wilson was already aware of its existence. Wilson is not only aware of the existence of Marvel, the Fox X-Men, and the Disney-owned [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]], he also understands and references the real-life circumstances of their coexistence and is aware that his franchise has been acquired by Disney, even adhering to specific guidelines set by [[Kevin Feige]]. Wilson is aware of the existence of the [[Avengers]], [[Thor]], and [[Steve Rogers|Captain America]] despite their complete absence from his universe, mistaking a [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Johnny Storm]] Variant for Steve Rogers, with whom he bears a striking, uncanny resemblance. Before encountering [[Alioth]], Wilson was already aware that it first appeared and existed in [[Journey Into Mystery|''Loki'', Season 1 Episode 5]]. He was also aware of the Wolverine's blue-yellow [[Wolverine Suit|suit]] and the classic {{WPS|John Byrne (comics)|John Byrne}} one, both styles are also absent from the [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]] of his [[Earth-10005|universe]]. This multiversal awareness extends beyond the aforementioned timelines as he was also aware of all the cinematic [[Hub:Frank Castle|Punishers]] that existed in other film franchises. Wilson understands that the people existing in his reality are characters portrayed by actors and is able to explain reasons for inconsistencies in his world due to budgetary or practicality constraints in the real world. Deadpool is also able to communicate his thoughts with the audience members watching his adventures and has been shown to be able to interact with the "cameraman" broadcasting his reality. This power also provides Wilson with limited precognition, giving him the ability to predict or foreshadow certain events that fit narratively within his story, as well as events that transpire in the real world, such as the death of the Wolverine in his universe, even though it would occur in the not-too-distant future.

===Abilities===
{{Quote|I'm gonna fight you now.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''Master Martial Artist''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (81).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool blocks a [[Minutemen|Minuteman]]'s attack]] Due to his special forces training, Wilson is highly skilled in unarmed combat. As a result of his unpredictable nature, Wilson is highly dangerous in combat. Wilson's overall fighting style incorporates {{WPS|Karate}}, {{WPS|Ninjutsu}}, {{WPS|Taekwondo}}, {{WPS|Boxing}}, {{WPS|Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu}}, and {{WPS|Niten Ichi-ryū}}. Wilson was able to kill several Minutemen with the adamantium bones of the former variation of [[Wolverine]]. He later engaged in duels against with Variants of Wolverine several times; however, he was consistently outmatched by the latter due to his extensive combat experience. Regardless, when greatly enraged and focused, he dueled Wolverine throughout the night and equaled him in skill.
*'''Sword Mastery''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (89).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool blocks [[Wolverine]]'s strike]] Wilson is a highly trained swordsman. His swords allow him to cut through several trained shooters with ease. He was able to kill several TVA Minutemen using his dual katanas. Wilson used his swordsmanship skills to fight against Wolverine, who only survived Wilson's multiple stab wounds due to his healing factor. He was able to kill the Minuteman leader by ricocheting one of his swords with a single strike.
{{Quote|[[Baby Knife|Baby knife]]!|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}} 
*'''Knife Mastery''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Trailer (111).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool stabbing [[Wolverine]]]] Wilson is highly skilled at using knives in combat. He used a knife to stab [[Wolverine]] during both of their fights. Wilson also demonstrated knife-throwing skills, such as when he dug up Logan's corpse and used some of his bones as throwing projectiles to kill multiple TVA agents.
*'''Nunchaku Mastery''': Wilson has demonstrated proficiency with nunchucks. After digging up [[Logan|Logan's]] corpse, Wilson used Logan's adamantium bones as a pair of nunchucks to kill multiple TVA Minutemen.
{{Quote|Unless you want to take a deep breath through your fucking forehead, I suggest you reconsider.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''Master Marksman''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (83).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool throwing bones at [[Minutemen]]]] Because of his special forces training, Wilson is highly proficient with firearms. Wilson typically prefers dual pistols while shooting in combat. He was able to shoot Wolverine and multiple members of the [[Deadpool Corps]] with great accuracy, all of whom only survived due to their healing factors.
{{Quote|I blew it. After all that the only they're gonna remember is that god awful dismount.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''Master Acrobat''': [[File:Deadpool & Wolverine Teaser Trailer (108).png|thumb|250px|Deadpool acrobatically attacking a soldier]] Wilson's enhanced reflexes and agility make him highly evasive and mobile in battle. He is capable of performing complex aerial movements while in combat. Using a variety of free-running and parkour maneuvers, Wilson is challenging to anticipate with his erratic and spontaneous movement.
{{Quote|I know how to fuck people up for money, but you, you know how to save them.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''Master Assassin''': Wilson is an extremely skilled assassin. His special forces training combined with his trait of talking too much gained him the nickname of "Merc with a Mouth." Wilson was able to kill several TVA Minutemen using only Logan's adamantium bones.

==Equipment==
===Weapons===
{{Quote|Get my [[Canada|country]]'s name out of your fucking mouth! And my [[Deadpool's Katanas|sword]]. Give me that.|Deadpool to Minuteman Leader|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''[[Deadpool's Katanas|Twin Katanas]]''': Wilson carries two katanas made of [[adamantium]] on his back created by the TVA. He used these swords to kill multiple Minutemen and fight against Wolverine. He later used these swords to fight against members of the [[Deadpool Corps]].
{{Quote|And all I have to remember [[Nicepool|him]] by are these two gold-plated, .50-caliber Desert Eagle pistoleros.|Deadpool to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*[[File:Deadpool with two golden guns.png|thumb|250px|Deadpool wielding {{WPS|Desert Eagle}} pistols]]'''[[Deadpool's Twin Guns|Desert Eagle Mark XIX]]''': Wilson uses a pair of .50 AE pistols when operating as Deadpool. He utilized these pistols while [[Duel in the Void|fighting Wolverine]], but the latter sliced the barrels of the pistols with his claws. After [[Nicepool|Nicepool's]] death, he used his pair of gold plated Desert Eagle pistols to [[Attack on Earth-10005|fight]] against the [[Deadpool Corps]] with Wolverine.
{{Quote|This is baby knife. She's gonna fuck you in the face now.|Deadpool to [[Cassandra Nova]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''[[Baby Knife|SOG Daggert 2 Combat Knife]]''': Wilson carries this combat knife holstered in his right boot, which he dubbed as “Baby Knife.” Wilson used it to fight against Wolverine twice and when attempting to kill Cassandra Nova.
*'''Benchmark Punch Daggers''': Wilson carries a pair of punch daggers sheathed on the pectoral area of his suit, which he used to fight against Wolverine. The punch daggers are more commonly used in close-quarters combat in case the twin katanas are less effective, such as in his [[Duel in Ol' Betsy|fight]] with Wolverine in the ''[[Ol' Betsy]]''.
*'''[[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]]'s Corpse''': In an effort to salvage the Anchor Being of his universe, that being Wolverine, Wilson exhumed his body from its resting place only to find it completely skeletonized. Confronted by the [[Time Variance Authority|TVA]]'s [[Minutemen]], he improvised weapons using Wolverine's bones, such as nunchucks, maces, shuriken and gauntlets bearing his claws, using their [[adamantium]] composition to his advantage.

===Other Equipment===
{{Quote|So what made you finally wear an honest to god [[Wolverine Suit|costume]]? [[Deadpool Suit|Mine]]'s red so they can't see me bleed. But I can see how yellow would be useful too.|Wade Wilson to [[Wolverine]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
[[File:Deadpool (D&W).jpg|thumb|250px|Wilson in his new suit]]
*'''[[Deadpool Suit]]''': Wilson wears a red and black suit when operating as the mercenary Deadpool to hide his disfigured form. Wilson designed the suit to be red so that his enemies wouldn't be able to tell if he was bleeding when he got injured. After being taken from his reality by [[Paradox]], Wade received an upgraded version of his costume with a brighter red and brighter black.
*'''[[TemPad]]''': Wade used a TemPad that he stole from [[Paradox]] after learning about his plan to speed up his world's destruction, leading him on a mission to find a Wolverine that can become his world's new anchor being. The TemPad was lost after Deadpool was pruned by Mr. Paradox into the Void, although he seemingly gained a new one, which he used to show the footage that proved that [[Human Torch/Void-Analyzing Fantastic Four|Johnny Storm]] did insult [[Cassandra Nova]].

===Former Equipment===
{{Quote|Is this because I used {{WPS|Cable (character)#Film|Cable}}'s [[Cable's Time-Travel Device|time machine]]? I brought a couple of people back to life and then I destroyed it.|Wade Wilson to [[Mr. Paradox]]|Deadpool & Wolverine}}
*'''[[Cable's Time-Travel Device]]''': Wade used a time-travel device owned by {{WPS|Cable (character)#Film|Cable}} to reverse the deaths of his now ex-fiancée [[Vanessa Carlysle]], alongside two members of the {{WPS|X-Force#Film|X-Force}}, [[Peter Wisdom]] and [[Shatterstar]]. He later used it to kill a [[Weapon XI|Variant]] of himself before that Variant could fight against [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]] and [[Ryan Reynolds]] before he could sign for {{WPS|Green Lantern (film)|Green Lantern}}. He also used the device to visit the [[Sacred Timeline]] in an attempt to join the [[Avengers]] but was ultimately turned down, leading him into a depressive spiral that led to the device being destroyed.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Wade Wilson's Apartment|Apartment]]''': Wade currently resides in an apartment located in [[New York City]].
*'''[[Drive Max]]''': Wade formerly worked at Drive Max after being rejected from joining the [[Avengers]] by [[Happy Hogan]]. Upon teaming up with a [[Wolverine|Variant]] of [[Wolverine/Earth-10005|Wolverine]], he quit his job and returned as Deadpool.
*'''[[Time Variance Authority Office]]''': Wade was brought to the Time Variance Authority by [[Paradox]], per his superior's requests, as they believed he's special and is needed in battling against a "grizzly fate sometime in the future". After the crisis revolving the [[Time Ripper]] was resolved, Wade continued to work for the TVA.

